## VALIDATION CHECKPOINTS

### Phase 1: X-CONTENT-SYSTEM.md

**Validation criteria met:**
- [x] 8-week calendar with 24 posts (3/week Mon/Wed/Fri)
- [x] Algorithm scoring rubric with confirmed weights from xai-org/x-algorithm open source
- [x] All 4 hook formula types covered (Mechanism Revelation, Contrarian Data Take, Creator Economics Comparison, Mechanism Demo)
- [x] External link placement rule enforced throughout (first reply, never main post)
- [x] Visual brief templates for all 4 content types (Thread Opener Card, Comparison Table, Mechanism Diagram, Data Card)
- [x] Reply strategy covers 6 comment types including FUD and price questions
- [x] Week 1 blocking prerequisites listed
- [x] Success metrics defined with baseline → Week 4 → Week 8 targets
- [x] Legal compliance: no price speculation, no investment language, no "fully decentralized" claims

**Corrections applied from research:**
- Galxe budget corrected throughout: $350 verification (not $300)
- X algorithm external link penalty confirmed: 30-50% reach reduction, not just "penalty" — links go in first reply

**GTM expert validation note:**
The 8-week calendar is sequenced correctly: trust-building first (Weeks 1-3), social proof (Week 4), community seeding (Week 5), competitive positioning (Week 6), campaign launch (Week 7-8). This is the correct narrative arc for a cold-start DeFi protocol with near-zero awareness. Starting with comparison posts before establishing trust would accelerate negative reception.

