### Phase 2: TELEGRAM-PLAYBOOK.md

**Validation criteria met:**
- [x] Community rules (6 rules, enforceable)
- [x] 3-message welcome sequence (0s / 30s / 5min automated)
- [x] Weekly cadence (Mon/Wed/Fri, template per day)
- [x] Buybot spec (Rose Bot primary, Combot alternative — with configuration detail)
- [x] Outreach list (Tier 1 and Tier 2 groups identified)
- [x] Moderator handbook (escalation matrix, response templates)
- [x] AMA protocol (setup, execution, closing)
- [x] 8-week growth targets
- [x] Buybot decision logic (NOT during Phase 1 — correctly deferred)

**GTM expert validation note:**
The decision to NOT run a buybot during Phase 1 is correct. Running a buybot that posts "$2 buy" announcements would be a trust-killer, not a trust-builder. The mechanics-first approach requires the community tone to match the protocol's technical credibility. Buybot is for hype phases, not foundation phases.

