### Phase 3: GALXE-CAMPAIGN.md

**Validation criteria met:**
- [x] Corrected budget breakdown ($300 + $350 + $350 = $1,000)
- [x] 3-tier architecture (social → wallet → on-chain)
- [x] Sybil gate correctly specified (BAB Token, NOT Gitcoin Passport)
- [x] USDC reward currency (NOT OKS — 5.7M OKS at current price is a signal-killer)
- [x] Galxe Space setup instructions (step-by-step)
- [x] BNB Chain Project Spotlight submission included
- [x] Anti-farming tactics (quiz, manual Tier 3 review, no referral multipliers)
- [x] Success metrics with realistic ranges (200-400 Tier 1, 15-40 Tier 3)
- [x] Post-campaign actions defined (wallet export, Tier 3 personal DMs)
- [x] Campaign timing aligned with X calendar (Week 5 prep, Week 7 launch)

**Correction flag — budget discrepancy (resolved):**
Original project plan budgeted $300 for Galxe verification. Actual price is $350/year. This reduces reward pool from $400 to $350. All budget tables in GALXE-CAMPAIGN.md and OIKOS-GTM-MASTER.md use the corrected figures.

**GTM expert validation note:**
The Tier 1 quiz is the most underrated element of this design. Most Galxe campaigns skip the quiz because it lowers completion rates. For Oikos, a lower Tier 1 completion rate with higher quiz pass quality is the correct tradeoff. The goal is 200 qualified users, not 2,000 farmers. The quiz filters the difference.

