### Phase 4: DISCORD-ENGAGES.md

**Validation criteria met:**
- [x] Discord server decision framework (prerequisite — check state before committing)
- [x] 5-quest sequence with completion estimates and role mapping
- [x] Role structure (Lurker → Learner → Builder → Founder → Moderator)
- [x] Engages limitation noted (cannot do on-chain verification — Galxe handles that)
- [x] Channel structure (minimum viable for solo marketer)
- [x] Integration checklist (Discord + Engages + Galxe cross-reference)
- [x] Content per stage (pre-launch standby → Galxe launch → post-Galxe community mode)
- [x] Moderator handbook (escalation matrix matches Telegram)
- [x] Success metrics

**GTM expert validation note:**
The Discord prerequisite check is the most important element of this phase. Launching an Engages campaign on a dead Discord is a waste of setup time and sends a ghost-town signal to any users who click through. The explicit decision tree (< 10 / 10-50 / 50+) gives Daniel a clear decision rule without requiring judgment in the moment.

