### Phase 5: KOL-OUTREACH.md

**Validation criteria met:**
- [x] 10-target shortlist structured by category (Tier A/B/C)
- [x] Search methodology (X advanced search queries, verification steps)
- [x] 3 outreach templates (Creator Economics Pitch, Co-Launch Pitch, Media Feature)
- [x] Compensation hierarchy (co-launch > whitelist > milestone cash)
- [x] Milestone payment structure ($100/$150/$100 = $350 max per KOL)
- [x] Disclosure contract template (Appendix A)
- [x] Four.meme infiltration tactic (Telegram community, engagement-first approach)
- [x] BSC Daily media buy (pay-for-placement, execute Week 7+)
- [x] Tracking sheet columns defined
- [x] Sequencing enforced: outreach starts Week 7, not earlier

**GTM expert validation note:**
The co-launch model (Tier C) is the highest-leverage and most underutilized tactic in this system. A KOL who launches their own community token on Oikos is not a promoter — they're a creator with economic skin in the game. Their incentive to explain the protocol accurately is higher than any paid promo model. Finding even 3 Tier C targets who successfully launch in Phase 1 would deliver more authentic reach than any combination of paid KOL posts.

**Legal validation:**
The disclosure contract template includes all required elements for FTC compliance (paid partnership disclosure) and avoids SEC-adjacent language (no performance guarantees, no investment framing). Must still be reviewed by a DeFi-familiar attorney before first use.

